Roger. I had expected `vim.lsp.set_log_level("debug")` to be in the [minimal_init.lua file](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/master/test/minimal_init.lua). Thanks for all the pointers.

Putting down the basic CMakeLists.txt:
```
project("ulp_close")
add_executable(prog main.cpp)
```

and then running `cmake . -DCMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS=ON` it generated a compile_commands.json as:
```
[
{
  "directory": "/home/s1000586/code/cpp_practice/ulp_close",
  "command": "/usr/bin/c++      -o CMakeFiles/prog.dir/main.cpp.o -c /home/s1000586/code/cpp_practice/ulp_close/main.cpp",
  "file": "/home/s1000586/code/cpp_practice/ulp_close/main.cpp"
}
]
```

But the behaviour of `neovim -u minimal_init.lua main.cpp` is identical. The logfile now spits out:
